# IntelliJ HTTP Client examples for technical-interview-demo
# User profile requests require an authenticated session.
# Missing-session responses use the same localized ProblemDetail shape as other API errors.
# Unsafe writes also require X-XSRF-TOKEN mirrored from the XSRF-TOKEN cookie
# bootstrapped by GET /api/session.
# Use authentication.http first when you need to obtain or refresh sessionCookie through the
# supported bootstrap/login/logout flow.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@csrfToken = not-captured-run-setup-first
@sessionCookie = paste-technical-interview-demo-session-here
# csrfToken is populated automatically by the bootstrap request below.

### UserAccountController - bootstrap authenticated CSRF token
# Run this after login and again after logout or a fresh login before unsafe writes.
# This is the supported refresh step before `PUT /api/account/language`.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/session
Cookie: technical-interview-demo-session={{sessionCookie}}
Accept: application/json

> {%
    const csrfCookie = response.cookiesByName("XSRF-TOKEN")[0];
    if (csrfCookie) {
        client.global.set("csrfToken", csrfCookie.value);
        client.log("Captured XSRF-TOKEN from response.");
    } else {
        client.log("XSRF-TOKEN cookie not found in response. Using existing global csrfToken if available.");
    }
%}

### UserAccountController - current authenticated user
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/account
Cookie: technical-interview-demo-session={{sessionCookie}}
Accept: application/json

### UserAccountController - current authenticated user without session (401 localized ProblemDetail)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/account
Accept: application/problem+json

### UserAccountController - update preferred language (authenticated session)
# Run the bootstrap request above first to populate csrfToken automatically.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/account/language
Cookie: technical-interview-demo-session={{sessionCookie}}
X-XSRF-TOKEN: {{csrfToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "preferredLanguage": "pl"
}
